Sentencas: In this study, PrBa0.5Sr0.5Fe1.9Ge0.1O5+delta (PBSFG), the Sr and Ge doped PrBaFe2O5+delta (PBF), is investigated as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide cells (SOCs).
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis

Sentencas: PBSFG has the potential to be a promising symmetrical electrode in SOCs owing to its high catalytic performance with redox stability.
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis

Sentencas: The concentration of oxygen vacancies and surface exchange coefficient of PBSFG are better than that of PBF.
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis

Sentencas: The results indicate that PBSFG exhibits not only adequate performance in the fuel cell, with a maximum power density of 1.05 W cm(-2) at 800 degree celsius, but also enhanced CO2 electrolysis performance, compared to the PBF.
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis

Sentencas: Specifically, in the CO2-electrolysis mode, a maximum current density of 825 mA cm(-2) is measured at 850 degree celsius and 1.5 V, which is substantially higher than that of 370 mA cm(-2) measured for undoped PBF.
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis

Sentencas: These results demonstrate the effectiveness of Sr and Ge doping in PBF to improved CO2 electrolysis performance and notable fuel cell performance.
Titulo: A-site and B-site co-doped PrBaFe2O5+δ double perovskite as a symmetrical electrode of solid oxide fuel cell with potential of CO2 electrolysis
